<TITLE> FBCCI finalises candidatures </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 2 (bdnews24.com)  The candidates for FBCCI's next board of directors for 2010-12 have been finalised ahead of its elections scheduled June 17. The board of directors' secretary Afsarul Arefin told bdnews24.com on Wednesday that 74 candidates for 44 posts were found 'qualified'. Tuesday was the last day for scrutinising and withdrawing nomination papers. A total of 98 candidates submitted their nomination papers, Arefin said. A total of 21 candidates withdrew their candidature and another three were cancelled by the election arbitration board, he said. Regarding cancellation of three candidatures, he said their nomination papers for the post of director were cancelled because they had held the position on three previous tenures. These three candidates are FBCCI's first vice president Abul Kashem Ahmed and directors Bazlur Rahman and Shamsul Alam. Of the 74 valid candidates, eight from chamber group and another eight from association group have already been nominated as 'directors'. A total of 58 candidates are contesting for 28 posts. Of them, a total of 38 from associations will be contesting the elections for 14 director posts while 20 from chambers will be contesting the elections for 14 director posts. Elections to the country's apex business body, the Federation of Bangladesh Chambers of Commerce and Industries board of directors for 2010-12 will be held on June 17 and then on June 19. The FBCCI's three top office bearers  president, first vice president and vice president  will be elected by 28 elected and 16 nominated directors. 
